obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (46911)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Societies formed by memorandum of association and registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46911&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `Any seven or more`
  line `persons associated for any literary, scientific, or charitable purpose, or for any such purpose as is`
  line `described in section 20 of this Act, may, by subscribing their names to a memorandum of association, and`
  line `filing the same with the Registrar of Joint-stock Companies ^1***, form themselves into a society under`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section before section 1, Act 21 of 1860.--In the Societies Registration Act, 1860`
  line `(21 of 1860) (hereinafter referred to as the said Act), section 1 shall be renumbered as section 1-A and`
  line `before the said section as so renumbered, the following new section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `1. Appointment of Registrar of Societies.--The State Government may, by notification, appoint a`
  line `person to be called the Registrar of Societies and he shall exercise such powers and perform such duties`
  line `and functions as are conferred by or under the provisions of this Act, and shall subject to such general or`
  line `special order as the State Government may from time to time make, superintend the administration and`
  line `carry out the provisions of this Act throughout the State or Orissa.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 21 of 1958, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Adaptation.--In the said Act, for the expressions, Registrar of Joint Stock Companies and`
  line `Registrar wherever they occur, the expression Registrar of Societies shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 21 of 1958, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Pending proceedings and construction of reference to Registrar of Companies in instruments`
  line `issued or made before this Act.--(1) All proceedings under the said Act pending before the Registrar of`
  line `Joint Stock Companies at the date of commencement of this Act shall stand transferred to the Registrar of`
  line `Societies and any such proceedings shall be continued and disposed of by the Registrar of Societies, as if`
  line `it had been originally instituted before such Registrar under the said Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In all certificates of registration and in all rules or bye-laws of societies and in all other`
  line `instruments issued or made under the said Act before the date of commencement of this Act, references to`
  line `the Registrar of Joint Stock Companies or the Registrar of Companies shall be deemed to be and be`
  line `construed as references to the Registrar of Societies.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 21 of 1958, s. 4]`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 1.--In the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860), as applicable to the`
  line `State of Orissa , section 1 shall be renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof and after sub-section (1) as so`
  line `renumbered, the following sub-sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) The State Government may, by notification, appoint one or more Additional Registrars with such`
  line `local jurisdiction as may be assigned to them by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Additional Registrars so appointed shall, subject to the control of the Registrar of Societies,`
  line `exercise such of the powers and perform such of the functions of the Registrar of Societies as the State`
  line `Government may authorize in that behalf.".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 9 of 1979, s. 2]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Union territory of Ladakh`
  line
  line `After the preamble and before the existing section 1, insert--`
  line
  line `"1. Appointment, etc. of Registrar of Societies, etc.--(1) The Administration of Union territory`
  line `of Ladakh may, by notification, appoint a person to be called the Registrar of Societies and he shall`
  line `exercise such powers and perform such duties and functions as are conferred by or under the`
  line `provisions of this Act, and shall subject to such general or special order as the Administration of the`
  line `Union territory of Ladakh may from time to time make, superintend the administration and carry out`
  line `the provisions of this Act throughout the Union territory of Ladakh.";`
  line
  line `"(2) The Administration of the Union territory of Ladakh may by notification, appoint one or`
  line `more Additional Registrars with such local jurisdiction as may be assigned to them.`
  line
  line `(3) The Additional Registrars so appointed shall, subject to the control of the Registrar of`
  line `Societies, exercise such of the powers and perform such of the functions of the Registrar of Societies`
  line `as the Administration of the Union territory of Ladakh may authorise in that behalf.";`
  line
  line `(b) number the existing section as section 1A and in this section as so numbered, for`
  line `"Registrar of Joint-Stock Companies" substitute "Registrar of Societies.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Second Order, 2020, vide`
  line `Notification No. S.O. 3805(E), dated (26-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `After section 1, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Definitions-1A. --In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires:--`
  line
  line `(a) "Administrator" means the Administrator of the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh`
  line `appointed by the President under Article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) "Registrar" means the Registrar of Societies appointed by the Administrator."`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 6 of 1978, s. 2 and the schedule]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand
  line
  line `Substitution of section 1.--In Societies Registration Act 1860, (which is hereinafter referred to as`
  line `Principal Act) the section 1 shall be substituted as follows, namely:--`
  line
  line `"1. Societies formed by memorandum of association and registration.---Any seven or more`
  line `persons associated for any literary, scientific or charitable purpose, or for any such purpose as is`
  line `described in section 20 of the Act, may, be digital signature of their name in online form of`
  line `Memorandum of Association and rules filling the same online with the Registrar form themselves`
  line `into a society under this Act.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 4 of 2019, s. 2]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Insertion of section 1A in Central Act 21 of 1860.--After section 1 of the Societies Registration Act,`
  line `1860 (hereinafter called the principal Act), The following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"1A. Definitions.-- In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "State Government" means the Government of the State of Haryana.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 14 of 2007, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figures "under Act 19 of 1857" rep. by Act 16 of 1874, s. 1 and Sch., Pt. I. See now the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of`
  line `1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (46912)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Memorandum of association.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46912&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The memorandum of association shall contain the following`
  line `things (that is to say)--`
  line
  line `the name of the society;`
  line
  line `the objects of the society;`
  line
  line `the names, addresses, and occupations of the governors, council, directors, committee, or other`
  line `governing body to whom, by the rules of the society, the management of its affairs is entrusted.`
  line
  line `A copy of the rules and regulations of the society, certified to be a correct copy by not less than`
  line `three of the members of the governing body, shall be filed with the memorandum of association.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (46913)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Registration and fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46913&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^13. Registration and fees.--Upon such memorandum and certified copy being filed, the Registrar`
  line `shall certify under his hand that the society is registered under this Act. There shall be paid to the`
  line `Registrar for every such registration fee of fifty rupees, or such smaller fee as ^2[the State Government]`
  line `may, from time to time, direct; and all fees so paid shall be accounted for to ^3[the State Government].`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Insertion of a new section.--In the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the principal Act), after Section 3, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `3-A. Prohibition against registration of societies with undesirable names.--No society shall be`
  line `registered by a name which, in the opinion of the Registrar of Societies is undesirable , being a name`
  line `identical with or, which in the opinion of the Registrar of Societies so nearly resembles the name by`
  line `which any other existing society has been previously registered under this Act or anybody corporate`
  line `which has been incorporated or registered under any other law for the time being in force as to be likely`
  line `to deceive the public or members of either society or anybody corporate, or which, without the previous`
  line `permission of the Government concerned , suggests or is calculated to suggest the patronage of that`
  line `Government or connection with anybody constituted by that Government or any local authority, or`
  line `which may, subject to any rules made in that behalf, be deemed to be undesirable by the Registrar of`
  line `Societies.".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Odisha Act 6 of 2013, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Union territory of Ladakh`
  line
  line `Section 3.--For "Registrar", substitute "Registrar of Societies."`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Second Order, 2020, vide`
  line `Notification No. S.O.3805(E), dated (26-10-2020).]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3.--In Principal Act sub-section (1) of section 3 of shall be substituted as`
  line `follows, namely:--`
  line
  line `"3. Registration and fees.--(1) Upon such memorandum and its digitally signed copy being`
  line `filed alongwith particulars of the address of Society office which will be registered address, by the`
  line `secretary of the society on behalf of the persons subscribing to the memorandum, the Registrar shall`
  line `certify under his digital signature that the society is registered under this Act, For every such`
  line `registration fees of five thousand five hundred and fifty rupees shall be paid to Registrar. For every`
  line `such registration for Youth/Women Mangal Dal, Women Group/Community Group fees of fifty`
  line `rupees shall be paid.`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, increase`
  line `from time to time the fee payable under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Registrar may, in his discretion, issue public offline notice or issue`
  line `offline notice to such persons as he thinks fit inviting offline objections, if any against the proposed`
  line `registration and consider all objections that may be received by him before registering the society.`
  line
  line `The prescribed fee of registration shall be submitted online after the online approval of`
  line `registration by the Registrar. After depositing the prescribed fees, the digitally signed Society`
  line `Registration Certificate shall be downloaded by the applicant.`
  line
  line `[VideUttarakhand Act 4 of 2019, s. 3]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 3 of Central Act 21 of 1860.-- In Section 3 of the Societies Registration Act,`
  line `1860 (hereinafter called the principal Act), for the words "fifty rupees", the words "two hundred and fifty`
  line `rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 14 of 2001, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Insertion of section 3A in Central Act 21 of 1860.--After section 3 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"3A. Refusal of registration.--(1) The Registrar may, in his discretion, issue public notice or`
  line `issue notice to such persons as he thinks fit inviting objections, if any, against the proposed`
  line `registration and consider all objections that may be received by him before registering the society.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 3, the Registrar shall refuse to register a`
  line `society, if after giving it an opportunity of showing cause against such refusal, he is satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(a) the name of the society is identical with that of any other society previously registered`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the name of the society sought to be registered uses any of the words, namely:-- "Union",`
  line `"State", "Land Mortgage", "Land development", "Co-operative", "Gandhi", "Reserve Bank" or any`
  line `words expressing or implying the sanction. Approval or patronage of the Central or any State`
  line `Government or any word which suggests or is calculated to suggest any connection with any`
  line `local authority or any corporation or body constituted by or under any law for the time being in`
  line `force or is such as is otherwise likely to deceive the public or the members of any other society`
  line `previously registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) anyone or more of the objects of the society sought to be registered is not an object`
  line `mentioned in section 1 and 20; or`
  line
  line `(d) its objects are contrary to any other law for the time being in force or contrary to public`
  line `policy.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 14 of 2007, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. This section was amended in its application to Berar by s. 14 of the Central Provinces and Berar Vidya Mandir Act, 1939`
  line `(C. P. & B. Act 3 of 1940).`
  line
  line `2. The words "the Governors-General of India in Council" have been successively adapted by the A.O. 1937 and the A.O. 1950`
  line `to read as above.`
  line
  line `3. The word "Govt." has been successively adapted by the A.O. 1937 and the A. O. 1950 to read as above.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (46914)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Annual list of managing body to be filed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46914&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Once in every year, on or before the fourteenth day`
  line `succeeding the day on which, according to the rules of the society, the annual general meeting of the`
  line `society is held, or, if the rules do not provide for an annual general meeting, in the month of January, a list`
  line `shall be filed with the Registrar of Joint-stock Companies, of the names, addresses and occupations of the`
  line `governors, council, directors, committee, or other governing body then entrusted with the management of`
  line `the affairs of the society.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 4A in Act XXI of 1860.-- After section 4 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `new section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"4A. Changes in managing body and rules to be filed.--(1) Together with the list mentioned in`
  line `section 4, there shall be sent to the Registrar of Joint Stock Companies a statement showing changes`
  line `during the year to which the list relates in the personnel of the governors, council, directors, committee or`
  line `other governing body to whom the management of the affairs of the society is entrusted and also a copy`
  line `of the rules of the society corrected up-to-date and certified to be a correct copy by not less than three of`
  line `the members of the governing body.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every alteration made in the rules of the society, certified to be a correct copy by not`
  line `less than three members of the governing body, shall be sent to the Registrar of Joint Stock Companies`
  line `within fifteen days of the making of such alterations."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam 11 of 1952, s. 2]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections 4-A, 4-B and 4-C, Act (21 of 1860).--In the Societies Registration Act,`
  line `1860 (21 of 1860) (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act) after section 4, the following new sections`
  line `shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `4-A Changes in the list mention 4 and rules to be filed.--(1) Without prejudice to the provisions`
  line `of section 4 any change in personnel on the list filed under the said section occurring during the year to`
  line `which such list relates shall be intimated to the Registrar or Societies within two months of such change.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every alteration made in the rules and regulations of the Society, certified to be a`
  line `correct copy by not less than three of the Governors, Directors or Members of the governing body, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be sent to the Registrar or Societies within two months of the making of such`
  line alteration.
  line
  line `4-B. Persons by whom lists, etc, are to be sent.--It shall be the duty--`
  line
  line `(a) Of the Chairman or, as the case may be, the President, the Secretary or any other person`
  line `authorized in that behalf by the rules and regulations of the Society or by a resolution of the governing`
  line `body of the Society; or`
  line
  line `(b) Of the Chairman or, as the case may be, the President of the governing body of the Society where`
  line `is no such authorization, to file the list mentioned in section 4, or to send the intimation or as the case may`
  line `be, the copy mentioned in section 4-A to the Registrar of Societies.`
  line
  line `4-C. Offence.--(1) If any person who is required so do to under the preceding section fails without`
  line `reasonable cause to comply with the provisions thereof, he shall, on conviction, be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person willfully makes or causes to be made any false entry or alternation in, or any`
  line `omission from, the list filed under section 4 or any statement or copy of rules and regulations sent to the`
  line `Registrar of Societies under section 4-A, he shall, on conviction, be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to five hundred rupees."`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 8 of 1969, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Union territory of Ladakh`
  line
  line `Section 4.--For "Registrar of Joint-Stock Companies", substitute "Registrar of Societies".`
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections--After section 4, insert the following sections, namely:--`
  line
  line `"4A. Changes in list mentioned in section 4 and rules to be filed.--(1) Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of section 4 and change in personnel on the list filed under said section occurring during`
  line `the year to which such list relates shall be intimated to the Registrar of Societies within two months of`
  line `the making of such changes.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every alteration made in the rules and regulation of the society, certified to be a`
  line `correct copy by not less than three of the Governors, Directors or members of governing body, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be sent to the Registrar of Societies within two months of such alteration.`
  line
  line `4B. Persons by whom lists, etc., are to be sent.--It shall be the duty--`
  line
  line `(a) of the Chairman or, as the case may be, the President, the Secretary or any other person`
  line `authorised in that behalf by the rules and regulations of the society or by a resolution of the`
  line `governing body of the society; or`
  line
  line `(b) of the Chairman, or as the case may be, the President of the governing body of the society`
  line `where there is no such authorisation,`
  line
  line `to file the list mentioned in section 4 or to send the intimation, or as the case may be, the copy`
  line `mentioned in section 4A to the Registrar of Societies.`
  line
  line `4C. Offence.--(1) If any person who is required so to do under the preceding section fails`
  line `without reasonable cause to comply with the provisions thereof, he shall, on conviction, be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person wilfully makes or causes to be made any false entry or alteration in, or any`
  line `omission from, the list filed under section 4 or any statement or copy of rules and regulations sent`
  line `to the Registrar of Societies under section 4A, he shall on, conviction, be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to five thousand rupees.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Second Order, 2020,`
  line `vide Notification No. S.O.3805(E), dated (26-10-2020).]/hr`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `After section 4, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"4A. Change in Managing Body and rules to be files.--(1) Together with the list mentioned, in`
  line `section 4, there shall be sent to the Registrar a statement showing changes during the year to which`
  line `the list relates in the personnel of the Governor, council, directors, committee or other governing`
  line `body to whom the management of the affairs of the societies is entrusted and also a copy of the rules`
  line `of the society corrected up-to-date and certified to be a correct copy by not less than three members of`
  line `the governing body.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every alteration made in the rules of the society certified to be a correct copy by not`
  line `less than three members of the governing body, shall be sent to the Registrar within fifteen days of`
  line `the making of such alteration."`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 6 of 1978, s. 2 and the schedule]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 4 of Central Act 21 of 1860.--In Section 4 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `words shall be added at the end, namely :--`
  line
  line `"There shall be paid to the Registrar for every list a fee of ten rupees.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 14 of 2001, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (46915)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Property of society how vested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46915&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The property, movable and immovable, belonging to a society`
  line `registered under this Act, if not vested in trustees, shall be deemed to be vested, for the time being, in the`
  line `governing body of such society, and in all proceedings, civil and criminal, may be described as the`
  line `property of the governing body of such society by their proper title.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Insertion of section 5A.--In Principal Act after section 5 the following section shall be inserted,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `"5A. Restriction on transfer of property.---(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law,`
  line `contract or other instrument, it shall not be lawful for the governing body of a society registered under`
  line `this Act or any of its members to transfer, without the previous approval of the court, any immovable`
  line `property belonging to any such society.`
  line
  line `(2) Every transfer made in contravention of sub-section (1) shall be void.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--For the purposes of this section the word court shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in section 13.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the purposes of this section the word transfer means--`
  line
  line `(d) a mortgage, charge, sale, gift or exchange.`
  line
  line `(e) lease for term exceeding five years; or`
  line
  line `(f) irrevocable licence."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 4 of 2019, s. 4]`
  line
  line `Omission of section 5-A of Act no. 21 of 1860.--Section 5-A of the Societies Registration Act, 1860`
  line `shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 23 of 2014, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (46916)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Suits by and against societies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46916&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Every society registered under this Act may sue or be sued in the`
  line `name of the president, chairman, or principal secretary, or trustees, as shall be determined by the rules and`
  line `regulations of the society, and, in default of such determination, in the name of such person as shall be`
  line `appointed by the governing body for the occasion:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be competent for any person having a claim or demand against the society, to`
  line `sue the president or chairman, or principal secretary or the trustees thereof, if on application to the`
  line `governing body some other officer or person be not nominated to be the defendant.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (46917)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Suits not to abate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46917&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No suit or proceeding in any Civil Court shall abate or discontinue by reason`
  line `of the person, by or against whom such suit or proceedings shall have been brought or continued, dying or`
  line `ceasing to fill the character in the name whereof he shall have sued or been sued, but the same suit or`
  line `proceeding shall be continued in the name of or against the successor of such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (46918)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Enforcement of judgment against society.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46918&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `If a judgment shall be recovered against the person`
  line `or officer named on behalf of the society, such judgment shall not be put in force against the property,`
  line `movable or immovable, or against the body of such person or officer, but against the property of the`
  line society.
  line
  line `The application for execution shall set forth the judgment, the fact of the party against whom it shall`
  line `have been recovered having sued or having been sued, as the case may be, on behalf of the society only,`
  line `and shall require to have the judgment enforced against the property of the society.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (46919)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Recovery of penalty accruing under bye-law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46919&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Whenever by any bye-law duly made in`
  line `accordance with the rules and regulations of the society, or, if the rules do not provide for the making of`
  line `bye-laws, by any bye-law made at a general meeting of the members of the society convened for the`
  line `purpose (for the making of which the concurrent votes of three-fifths of the members present at such`
  line `meeting shall be necessary), any pecuniary penalty is imposed for the breach of any rule or bye-law of the`
  line `society, such penalty, when accrued, may be recovered in any Court having jurisdiction where the`
  line `defendant shall reside, or the society shall be situate, as the governing body thereof shall deem expedient.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (46920)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Members liable to be sued as strangers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46920&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Any member who may be in arrear of a subscription`
  line `which according to the rules of the society he is bound to pay, or who shall possess himself of or detain`
  line `any property of the society in a manner or for a time contrary to such rules, or shall injure or destroy any`
  line `property of the society, may be sued for such arrear or for the damage accruing from such detention, injury,`
  line `or destruction of property in the manner hereinbefore provided.`
  line
  line `Recovery by successful defendant of costs adjudged.--But if the defendant shall be successful in`
  line `any suit or other proceeding brought against him at the instance of the society, and shall be adjudged to`
  line `recover his costs, he may elect to proceed to recover the same from the officer in whose name the suit`
  line `shall be brought, or from the society, and in the latter case shall have process against the property of the`
  line `said society in the manner above described.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (46921)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Members guilty of offences punishable as strangers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
