obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Any member who may be in arrear of a subscription`
  line `which according to the rules of the society he is bound to pay, or who shall possess himself of or detain`
  line `any property of the society in a manner or for a time contrary to such rules, or shall injure or destroy any`
  line `property of the society, may be sued for such arrear or for the damage accruing from such detention, injury,`
  line `or destruction of property in the manner hereinbefore provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (46922)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Societies enabled to alter, extend or abridge their purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46922&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it shall appear to the`
  line `governing body of any society registered under this Act, which has been established for any particular`
  line `purpose or purposes, that it is advisable to alter, extend, or abridge such purpose to or for other purposes`
  line `within the meaning of this Act, or to amalgamate such society either wholly or partially with any other`
  line `society, such governing body may submit the proposition to the members of the society in a written or`
  line `printed report, and may convene a special meeting for the consideration thereof according to the`
  line `regulations of the society;`
  line
  line `but no such proposition shall be carried into effect unless such report shall have been delivered or`
  line `sent by post to every member of the society ten days previous to the special meeting convened by the`
  line `governing body for the consideration thereof, nor unless such proposition shall have been agreed to by the`
  line `votes of three-fifths of the members delivered in person or by proxy, and confirmed by the votes of threefifths of the members present at a second special meeting convened by the governing body at an interval`
  line `of one month after the former meeting.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections 12A,12B and 12C in Act XXI of 1860.-- After section 12 of the Societies`
  line `Registration Act, 1860 (XXI of 1860), the following shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"12A. Change of name.--Any society registered under this Act may, with the consent of not less`
  line `than two-thirds of the total number of its members' by a resolution at a general meeting convened for`
  line `the purpose and subject to the provisions of section 12B, change its name.`
  line
  line `12B. Notice of change of name.--(1) Notice in writing of every change of name, signed by the`
  line `Secretary and, by seven members of the society changing its name, shall be sent to the Registrar;`
  line
  line `(2) If the proposed name is identical with that by which any other existing society has been`
  line `registered or, in the opinion of the Registrar, so nearly resembles such name as to be likely to deceive`
  line `the public, the Registrar shall refuse to register the change of name.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as provided in sub-section (2), the Registrar shall, if he is satisfied that the provisions of`
  line `this Act in respect of change of name have been complied with, register the change of name and the`
  line `change of name shall have effect from the date of such registration.`
  line
  line `12C. Effects of change of name.--The change in the name of a society registered under this Act`
  line `shall not affect any rights or obligations of the society or render defective any legal proceeding by or`
  line `against the society, and any legal proceeding which might have been continued or commenced by or`
  line `against it by its former name may be continued or commenced by or against it by its new name".`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 14 of 1948, s. 2]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of a section 12, Act (21 of 1860).--In section 12 of the principal Act--`
  line
  line `(a) in the first paragraph after the words "any other society" the words " or whenever the`
  line `governing body of any such society decides to change the name of the society" shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(b) after the second paragraph the following proviso shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Provided that no proposition for amalgamation shall be carried into effect unless it has been`
  line `considered, agreed to and confirmed by all the concerned societies in the manner prescribed in this`
  line `section".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 8 of 1969, s. 3]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections 12-A, 12-B and 12-C, Act 21 of 1860.--After section 12 of the principal`
  line `Act the following new sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `12-A. Registration of change of name.--(1) Where a proposition for change of name has been`
  line `agreed to and confirmed in the manner prescribed by section 12, a copy of the proposition so agreed to`
  line `and confirmed shall be forwarded to the Registrar of Societies for registering the change of name. If the`
  line `proposed name is identical with that by which any other existing society has been registered or in the`
  line `opinion of the Registrar so nearly resembles the name of such other society as is likely to deceive the`
  line `public or the members of either society, the Registrar shall refuse to register the change of name.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as provided in sub-section (1), the Registrar shall, if he is satisfied that the provisions of this`
  line `Act in respect of the change of name have been complied with, register the change of name and issue a`
  line `certificate of registration altered to meet the circumstances of the case. On the issue of such certificate the`
  line `change of name shall be complete.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall charge for any copy of a certificate issued under sub-section (2) a fee of rupee`
  line `one and all fees so paid shall be accounted for to the State Government.`
  line
  line `12-B. Effect of change of name.--The change in the name of a society shall not affect any rights or`
  line `obligations of the society or render defective any legal proceeding by or against the society; and any legal`
  line `proceeding which might have been continued or commenced by or against it by its former name may be`
  line `continued or commenced by or against it by the new name.`
  line
  line `12-C. Registration of change of name effected before commencement of the societies`
  line `Registration Amendment.--If any society registered under this Act has, before the date of the coming`
  line `into force of the Societies Registration (Orissa Amendment) Act, 1969 intimated to the Registrar the`
  line `change of its name and if the Registrar has recorded such change the Registrar may, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, on an application made by the society in this behalf and on payment of`
  line `fees as provided in sub-section (3) of section 12-A register the change of such name and issue a certificate`
  line `to the society under sub-section (2) of the said section. On the issue of such certificate the change shall be`
  line `deemed to be complete from the date on which such change was recorded by the Registrar."`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 8 of 1969, s. 4]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 12A.--In the principal Act, in section 12A,--`
  line
  line `(a) for sub-section (1), the following sub-sections shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) Where a proposition for change of name has been agreed to and confirmed in the manner`
  line `prescribed by section 12, a copy of the proposition so agreed to and confirmed shall be forwarded to`
  line `the Registrar of Societies for registering the change of name".`
  line
  line `(1A) The Registrar of Societies may refuse to register the change of name, if he is of the opinion`
  line `that the proposed change of name is undesirable for any of the reasons mentioned in section 3A.".`
  line
  line `(b) after sub-section (3), the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(4) if, through inadvertence or otherwise a society is registered by a name which is identical with`
  line `or, which in the opinion of the Registrar of Societies so nearly resembles the name by which any`
  line `other existing society has been previously registered under this Act or any body corporate which has`
  line `been incorporated or registered under any other law for the time being in force or any body`
  line `constituted by the Government or any local authority the Registrar of Societies may after hearing`
  line `the party concerned direct the society to change the name and the society shall change its name`
  line `within a period of three months from the date of issue of the direction in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act, or such longer period as the Registrar of Societies may think fit to allow.".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 6 of 2013, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Insertion of a new section.-- In the principal Act, after section 12-C, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `12-D. Registrar's power to cancel registration in certain circumstance.--(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, the Registrar may, be order in writing , cancel the registration of any`
  line `society on any of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the registration of the society, or its name or change of name is contrary to the provisions of`
  line `this Act or of any other law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) its activities or, opposed activities have been, or are subversive of the objects of the society or`
  line `proposed to public policy; or`
  line
  line `(c) the registration certificate has been obtained by misrepresentation of fact or fraud; or`
  line
  line `(d) the society fails to comply the direction issued under sub-section (4) of section 12-A:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of cancellation of registration of any society shall be passed until the society`
  line `has been given a reasonable opportunity of altering its name or objects or of showing cause against the`
  line `action proposed to be taken in regard to it.".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Act Orissa Act 6 of 2013, s. 4]`
  line
  line `Union territory of Ladakh`
  line
  line `Section 12.--`
  line
  line `(i) after "any other society", insert "or whenever the governing body of any such society decides`
  line `to change the name of the society"; and`
  line
  line `(ii) after the words "after the formal meeting" insert--`
  line
  line `"Provided that no proposition for amalgamation shall be carried into effect unless it has been`
  line `considered, agreed to and confirmed by all concerned societies in the manner prescribed in this`
  line `section.".`
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections--`
  line
  line `After section 12, insert--`
  line
  line `"12A. Registration of change of name.--(1) Where a proposition for change of name has`
  line `been agreed to and confirmed in the manner prescribed by section 12, a copy of the proposition`
  line `so agreed to and confirmed shall be forwarded to the Registrar for registering the change of name`
  line `and if the proposed change in the name is in his opinion undesirable for any of the reasons`
  line `mentioned in section 3A, the Registrar shall refuse to register the change of name.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as provided in sub-section (1), the Registrar shall, if he is satisfied that the`
  line `provisions of this Act in respect of change of name have been complied with, register the change`
  line `of name and issue a certificate of registration altered to meet the circumstances of the case, and`
  line `on the issue of such a certificate the change of name shall be complete.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall charge for any copy of a certificate issued under sub-section (2), a fee`
  line `of rupee five hundred and all fees so paid shall be accounted for to the Administration of the`
  line `Union territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `(4) If, through inadvertence or otherwise, a society is registered by a name which should not`
  line `have been registered (due regard being had to the provisions of section 3A), the Registrar may,`
  line `after hearing the party concerned direct the society to change the name; and the society shall`
  line `change its name within a period of three months from the date of the direction in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act, or such longer period as the Registrar may think fit to allow.`
  line
  line `12B. Effect of change of name.--The change in the name of society shall not affect any rights`
  line `or obligations of the society or render defective any legal proceeding by or against the society and`
  line `any legal proceeding which might have been continued or commenced by or against it by its`
  line `former name may be continued or commenced by or against it by its new name.`
  line
  line `12C. Maintenance of accounts and their balancing and accounting.--(1) Every governing`
  line `body entrusted with the management of the affairs of a society registered under this Act shall`
  line `keep regular accounts.`
  line
  line `(2) Such accounts shall be kept in such form as may be approved by the Registrar, and shall`
  line `contain such particulars as may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts shall be balanced each year on the 31st day of March or such other day as`
  line `may be fixed by the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts shall be audited annually in such manner as may be prescribed by rules and`
  line `by a person who is a Chartered Accountant within the meaning of the Chartered Accountants Act,`
  line `1949 (38 of 1949), or by such persons as may be authorised in this behalf by the Administration`
  line `of the Union territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `12D. Auditor's duty to prepare balance sheet and report irregularities, etc.--(1) It shall be`
  line `the duty of every auditor auditing the accounts of a society under section 12C to prepare balancesheet and income and expenditure account and to forward a copy of the same to the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(2) The auditor shall in his report specify all cases of irregular, illegal or improper`
  line `expenditure or failure or omission to recover money or other property belonging to the society or`
  line `of loss or waste of money or other property thereof, and state whether such expenditure, failure,`
  line `omission, loss or waste was caused in consequence of branch of trust or misapplication or any`
  line `other misconduct on the part of the governing body or any other person.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Second Order, 2020, vide`
  line `Notification No. S.O.3805(E), dated (26-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `After section 12, the following sections shall be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"12A. Change of name.--A society registered under this Act may, with the consent of not less than`
  line `two-thirds of the total number of its members, by a resolution, at a general meeting convened for the`
  line `purpose and subject to the provisions of section 12B change its name."`
  line
  line `"12B. Notice of change of name--(1) Notice in writing of every change of name, signed by the`
  line `Secretary and by seven members of the society, shall be sent to the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(2) If the proposed name is identical with that by which any other existing society has been registered`
  line `or, in the opinion of the Registrar, so nearly resembles such name as to be likely to deceive the public, the`
  line `Registrar shall refuse to register the change of name.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as provided in sub-section (2), the Registrar shall, if he is satisfied that the provisions of this`
  line `Act in respect of change of name shall have been complied with, register the change of name and the`
  line `change of name shall have effect from the date such registration.".`
  line
  line `"12C.Effect of change of name.--The change in the name of a society registered under this Act`
  line `shall not effect any right or obligation of the society or render defective any legal proceeding by or`
  line `against the society and any legal proceeding which might have been continued or commenced by or`
  line `against it by its former name may be continued or commenced by or against it by its changed name."`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 6 of 1978, s. 2 and the Schedule]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Insertion of section 12C, 12D and 12E in Central Act 21 of 1860.--After section 12B of the principal`
  line `Act, the following sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"12C. Maintenance of accounts and their balancing and auditing.--(1) Every governing body`
  line `entrusted with the management of the affairs of a society registered under this Act shall keep regular`
  line accounts.
  line
  line `(2) The accounts shall be kept in such form as may be approved by the Registrar, and shall`
  line `contain such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts shall be balanced each year on the 31st day of March or on such other day as`
  line `may be fixed by the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts shall be audited annually in such manner as may be prescribed and by a person`
  line `who is a chartered accountant within the meaning of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (Act 38 of`
  line `1949), or by such person as may be authorized in this behalf by the State Government.`
  line
  line `"12D. Auditor's duty to prepare balance sheet and report irregularities, etc.--(1) It shall be`
  line `the duty of every auditor auditing the accounts of a society under section 12C to prepare balance`
  line `sheet and income and expenditure account and to forward a copy of the same to the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(2) The auditor shall in his report specify all cases of irregular, illegal or improper expenditure or`
  line `failure or omission to recover money or other property belonging to the society or of loss or waste of`
  line `money or other property thereof, and state whether such expenditure, failure, omission, loss or waste`
  line `caused in consequence of breach of trust or misapplication or any other misconduct on the part of the`
  line `governing body or any other person.`
  line
  line `"12E. Registrar's power to cancel registration in certain circumstances.-- (1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, the Registrar may, by order in writing cancel the registration of any`
  line `society on any of the following grounds:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the registration of the society or of its name or change of name is contrary to the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) that its activities or proposed activities have been or are or will be subversive of the`
  line `objects of the society or opposed to public policy;`
  line
  line `(c) that the registration certificate has been obtained by misrepresentation or fraud;`
  line
  line `(d) that the society is carrying on any unlawful activity or allows unlawful activity to be`
  line `carried on within any premises under the control of the society:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of cancellation of registration of any society shall be passed until the`
  line `society has been given a reasonable opportunity of altering its name or object or of showing cause`
  line `against the action proposed to be taken in regard to it.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal against an order made under sub-section (1) may be preferred to such authority and`
  line `within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the authority under sub-section (2), shall be final.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 14 of 2007, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (46923)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Provision for dissolution of societies and adjustment of their affairs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46923&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Any number not less`
  line `than three-fifths of the members of any society may determine that it shall be dissolved, and thereupon it`
  line `shall be dissolved forthwith, or at the time then agreed upon, and all necessary steps shall be taken for the`
  line `disposal and settlement of the property of the society, its claims and liabilities, according to the rules of`
  line `the said society applicable thereto, if any, and, if not, then as the governing body shall find expedient`
  line `provided that, in the event of any dispute arising among the said governing body or the members of the`
  line `society, the adjustment of its affairs shall be referred to the principal Court of original civil jurisdiction of`
  line `the district in which the chief building of the society is situate; and the Court shall make such order in the`
  line `matter as it shall deem requisite:`
  line
  line `Provided that no society shall be dissolved unless three-fifths of the members shall have expressed a`
  line `wish for such dissolution by their votes delivered in person, or by proxy, at a general meeting convened`
  line `for the purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^1[whenever any Government] is a member of, or a contributor to, or otherwise`
  line `interested in any society registered under this Act, such society shall not be dissolved ^2[without the`
  line `consent of the Government of the State of registration].`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Amendment of section 13 of Act XXI of 1860.-- In section 13 of the said Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) after the words "as the governing body" the words "or special Committee formed to replace the`
  line `governing body in respect of all matters affecting the winding up of the affairs of the Society;" shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(b) after the words "the said governing body" the words "should it not have been replaced by the aforesaid`
  line `special Committee in respect of all matters affecting the winding up of the Society, or the said special`
  line `Committee," shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `(2) After section 13 of the Act, the following proviso shall be inserted as the first proviso, namely:--`
  line
  line `Provided that any matter decided by three-fifths of those present either in person or by proxy at any`
  line `meeting of the members of the Society or of the governing body thereof or of any special`
  line `Committee appointed at a General Meeting for the purpose of winding up of the affairs of a Society shall not be`
  line `deemed to be a matter of dispute within the meaning of this section.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 15 of 1948, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `In section 13:--`
  line
  line `(a) after the words "as the governing body", the words "or special committee formed to replace`
  line `the governing body in respect of all matters affecting the winding up of the affairs of the society"`
  line `shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(b) after the words "the said governing body", the words "should it have not been replaced by the`
  line `aforesaid special committee in respect of all matters affecting the winding up of the society, or the`
  line `said special committee" shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(c) in the second proviso, for the words "Government of the State of registration", the word`
  line `"Administrator" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(d) after the second proviso, the following further proviso shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `Provided further that any matter decided by three-fifth of those present either in person or by`
  line `proxy at any meeting of the members of the society or of any governing body thereof or of any`
  line `special committee appointed at a general meeting for the purpose of winding up of the affairs of a`
  line `society shall not be deemed to be a matter of dispute within the meaning of this section."`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 6 of 1978, s. 2 and the Schedule]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "whenever the Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid, for "without the consent of Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (46924)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Upon a dissolution no member to receive profit. Proviso for Joint-stock Companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46924&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If upon the dissolution of any society`
  line `registered under this Act there shall remain after the satisfaction of all its debts and liabilities any property`
  line `whatsoever, the same shall not be paid to or distributed among the members of the said society or any of`
  line `them, but shall be given to some other society, to be determined by the votes of not less than three-fifths`
  line `of the members present personally or by proxy at the time of the dissolution, or, in default thereof, by`
  line `such Court as aforesaid:`
  line
  line `Clause not to apply to Joint-stock Companies.--Provided, however, that this clause shall not apply`
  line `to any society which shall have been founded or established by the contributions of shareholders in the`
  line `nature of a Joint-stock Company.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Amendment of section 14 of Act XXI of 1860.-- In section 14 of the said Act, after the words "some`
  line `other society," the words "whether registered under this Act or not," shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 15 of 1948, s. 3]`
  line
  line Tripura
  line
  line `Amendment of Central Act XXI of 1860 by inserting a new section 14A--In its application to the Union`
  line `territory of Tripura, after section 14 insert the following new section, namely--`
  line
  line `14A. Disposal of property of a dissolved society.--Notwithstanding anything contained in section 14 it shall be`
  line `lawful for the members of any society dissolved under section 13 to determine by a majority of the votes of the`
  line `members present personally or by proxy at the time of the dissolution of such society that any property whatsoever`
  line `remaining after the satisfaction of all the debts and liabilities shall be given to the Government of Tripura to be`
  line `utilised for any of the purposes referred to in section 1.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 5 of 1969, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (46925)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Who is a Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46925&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act a member of a society`
  line `shall be a person who, having been admitted therein according to the rules and regulations thereof, shall`
  line `have paid a subscription, or shall have signed the roll or list of members thereof, and shall not have`
  line `resigned in accordance with such rules and regulations; but in all proceedings under this Act no person`
  line `shall be entitled to vote or be counted as a member whose subscription at the time shall have been in`
  line `arrear for a period exceeding three months.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (46926)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Governing body defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46926&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The governing body of the society shall be the governors, council,`
  line `directors, committee, trustees or other body to whom by the rules and regulations of the society the`
  line `management of its affairs is entrusted.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Amendment of section 16 of Central Act 21 of 1860.-- In section 16 of the principal Act, after the`
  line `words and signs "committee, trustees,", the words "trustee mandal" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 14 of 2007, s. 5]`
  line
  line `Insertion of section 16A in Central Act 21 of 1860.-- After section 16 of the principal Act, the`
  line `following section shall be inserted, namely: --`
  line
  line `"16A. Duties, functions and powers of governing body.-- The duties, functions and powers of`
  line `governing body of the society shall be such as may be prescribed.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 14 of 2007, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (46927)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Registration of societies formed before Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Rep. by the Indian Companies Act, 1866 (10 of 1866), s. 719, see now the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46927&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Any company or society established for a`
  line `literary, scientific, or charitable purpose, and registered under ^1Act 43 of 1850, or any such society`
  line `established and constituted previously to the passing of this Act but not registered under the said ^1Act 43`
  line `of 1850, may at any time hereafter be registered as a society under this Act; subject to the proviso that no`
  line `such company or society shall be registered under this Act unless an assent to its being so registered has`
  line `been given by three-fifths of the members present personally, or by proxy, at some general meeting`
  line `convened for that purpose by the governing body.`
  line
  line `In the case of a company or society registered under ^1Act 43 of 1850, the directors shall be deemed to`
  line `be such governing body.`
  line
  line `In the case of a society not so registered, if no such body shall have been constituted on the`
  line `establishment of the society, it shall be competent for the members thereof, upon due notice, to create for`
  line `itself a governing body to act for the society thenceforth.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (46928)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Such societies to file memorandum, etc., with Registrar of Joint-stock Companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46928&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `In order`
  line `to any such society as is mentioned in the last preceding section obtaining registry under this Act, it shall`
  line `be sufficient that the governing body file with the Registrar of Joint-stock Companies ^1*** a`
  line `memorandum showing the name of the society, the objects of the society, and the names, addresses and`
  line `occupations of the governing body, together with a copy of the rules and regulations of the society`
  line `certified as provided in section 2, and a copy of the report of the proceedings of the general meeting at`
  line `which the registration was resolved on.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Union territory of ladakh`
  line
  line `Section 18.--For "Registrar of Joint-Stock Companies", substitute "Registrar of Societies".`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Second Order, 2020, vide`
  line `Notification No. S.O. 3805(E), dated (26-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figures "under Act 19 of 1857", rep. by Act 16 of 1874, s. 1 and the Schedule, Pt. 1, see now the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (46929)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Inspection of documents, Certified copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46929&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Any person may inspect all documents filed with`
  line `the Registrar under this Act on payment of a fee of one rupee for each inspection; and any person may`
  line `require a copy or extract of any document or any part of any document, to be certified by the Registrar, on`
  line `payment of two annas for every hundred words of such copy or extract; and such certified copy shall be`
  line `prima facie evidence of the matters therein contained in all legal proceedings whatever.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Union territory of ladakh`
  line
  line `Section 19.--For "Registrar", substitute "Registrar of Societies.`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Second Order, 2020, vide`
  line `Notification No. S.O. 3805(E), dated (26-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `In section 19, for the words "two annas", the words fifteen paise" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 6 of 1978, s. 2 and the Schedule]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand
  line
  line `Substitution of section 19.--In Principal Act section 19 shall be substituted as follows, namely:--`
  line
  line `"19. Inspection of documents, Certified copies.--Any person may inspect all document files with`
  line `the Registrar under this act on payment of a fee of thee hundred rupees for each inspection; and any`
  line `person may require a digitally signed copy or extract of any documents or any part of any document or`
  line `any part of any documents, to be digitally certified by the Registrar on payment of rupees one hundred as`
  line `ordinary fee and rupees two such copy or extract and digital signed copy shall prima facie evidence of`
  line `the matters therein contained in all legal proceedings whatever.`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, increase from`
  line `time to time the fee payable under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 4 of 2019, s. 5]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 19 of Central Act 21 of 1860.-- In Section 19 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) for the words "one rupee", the words "twenty rupees" shall be substituted ; and`
  line
  line `(ii) for the words "twenty-five naye paise for every hundred words", the words "ten rupees per`
  line `page or part thereof" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 14 of 2001, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (46930)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `To what societies the Act shall apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 1927, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429&sectionId=46930&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_0_00011_186021_1523266592429
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The following societies may be registered under this Act:--`
  line
  line `Charitable societies, the military orphan funds or societies established at the several presidencies`
  line `of India, societies established for the promotion of science, literature, or the fine arts, for instruction,`
  line `the diffusion of useful knowledge, ^1[the diffusion of political education], the foundation or`
  line `maintenance of libraries or reading-rooms for general use among the members or open to the public,`
  line `or public museums and galleries of paintings and other works of art, collections of natural history,`
  line `mechanical and philosophical inventions, instruments, or designs.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections 21 and 22 in Act XXI of 1860.-- After section 20 of the principal Act, the`
  line `following new section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"21. Penalties.--(1) if the President, Secretary or any other person authorized in this behalf by a`
  line `resolution of the governing body of the society fails to comply with the provisions of section 4, he shall,`
  line `on conviction, be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and in case of a`
  line `continuing breach, shall also be punishable with fine not exceeding fifty rupees for each day, during the`
  line `period the breach continues after first conviction for such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person willfully makes or causes to be made any false entry in, or any omission from, the`
  line `list required by section 4, or in or from any statement of copy of rules or of alterations in rules sent to the`
  line `Registrar of Joint Stock Companies under section 4A, he shall, on conviction, be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to two thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `22. Procedure.--(1) No Court inferior to that of a Magistrate of the First Class shall try an offence`
  line `punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No Court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this Act except upon complaint`
  line `made by the Registrar of Joint Stock Companies or any other person, authorized in writing by him, in this`
  line behalf.--
  line
  line `[Vide Assam 11 of 1952, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `After section 20, the following sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"21. Penalties.--(1) If the President, Secretary or any other person authorised in this behalf by a`
  line `resolution of the governing body of the society fails to comply with the provisions of section 4A, he`
  line `shall, on conviction be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and in case of a`
  line `continuing breach, shall also be punishable with fine not exceeding fifty rupees for each day, during`
  line `the period the breach continue after the first conviction for such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person willfully makes or causes to be made any false entry in, or any commission from`
  line `the list required by section 4, or in or from any statement or copy of rules or of alterations in rules`
  line `sent to the Registrar under section 4A, he shall, on conviction, be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to two thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `22. Procedure.--(1) No court inferior to that of a Judicial Magistrate of the first class shall try`
  line `any offence punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Judicial Magistrate of the first class for the purposes of this Act means the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner, Additional Deputy Commissioner, Assistant Commissioner and Extra Assistant`
  line `Commissioner who has been empowered under the Assam Frontier (Administration of Just)`
  line `Regulation, 1945 (1 of 1945), to administer justice in the territory of Arunachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(2) No. court shall take congnizance of an offence punishable under this Act except upon`
  line `complaint made by the Registrar or any other person, authorised in writing by him, in this behalf."`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 6 of 1978, s. 2 and the Schedule]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Insertion of section 22 to 32 in Central Act 21 of 1860.-- After section 21 of the principal Act, the`
  line `following sections shall be added at the end, namely:--`
  line
  line `"22. Power of Registrar to call for information.--(1) The Registrar may, by written order,`
  line `require any society to furnish in writing such information or document within such time, being`
  line `ordinarily not less than three weeks from the date of receipt of the order by the society, as he may`
  line `specify in the order in connection with the affairs of the society or any documents filed by the society`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt by the society of an order under sub-section (1), it shall be the duty of the`
  line `President, Secretary or any other person authorized in this behalf to furnish such information or`
  line documents.
  line
  line `23. Investigations of affairs of society.-- (1) Where on the information received under section`
  line `22 or otherwise, the Registrar is of opinion that there is apprehension that the affairs of a society`
  line `registered under this Act are being so conducted as to defeat the objects of the society or that the`
  line `society or its governing body by whatever name called, or any office-bearer thereof in actual effective`
  line `control of the society is guilty of mismanaging its affairs or of any breach of fiduciary or other like`
  line `obligations, the Registrar may, either himself or by any person authorized by him in that behalf,`
  line `inspect or investigate into the affairs of the society or inspect any institution managed by the society.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of every office-bearer of the society when so required by the Registrar or`
  line `other person authorised under sub-section (1) to produce any books of account and other records of or`
  line `relating to the society which are in his custody and to give him all assistance in connection with such`
  line `inspection or investigation.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar or other person authorized under sub-section (1) may call upon and examine on`
  line `oath any office-bearer, member or employee of the society in relation to the affairs of the society and`
  line `it shall be the duty of every office-bearer, member or employee, when called upon, to appear before`
  line `him for such examination.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar or other person authorized under sub-section (1) may, if in his opinion it is`
  line `necessary for the purpose of inspection or investigation, seize any or all the records including account`
  line `books of the society:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person from whose custody such records are seized shall be entitled to make`
  line `copies thereof in the presence of the person seizing such records.`
  line
  line `(5) On the conclusion of the inspection or investigation, as the case may be, the person, if any,`
  line `appointed by the Registrar to inspect or investigate shall make a report to the Registrar on the result`
  line `of his inspection or investigation.`
  line
  line `(6) The Registrar may, after such inspection or investigation, give such directions to the society`
  line `or to its governing body or any office-bearer thereof, as he may think fit, for the removal of any`
  line `defects or irregularities within such time es may be specified and in the event of default in taking`
  line `action according to such directions, the Registrar may proceed to take action under section 12E or`
  line `section 30, as the case may he.`
  line
  line `24. Disputes regarding election of office-bearers.--(1) The prescribed authority may, on a`
  line `reference made to it by the Registrar or by at least one-fourth of the members of a society registered`
  line `in Haryana, beat and decide in a summary manner any doubt or dispute in respect of the election or`
  line `continuance in office of an office-bearer of such of society, and may pass such orders-in respect`
  line `thereof it deems fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the election of an office-bearer shall be set aside where the prescribed authority is`
  line satisfied--
  line
  line `(a) that any corrupt practice has been committed by such office bearer; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the nomination of any candidate has been improperly rejected; or`
  line
  line `(c) that the result of the election insofar as it concerns to such office-bearer has been`
  line `materially affected by the improper acceptance of any nomination or by the improper reception,`
  line `refusal or rejection of any vote or the reception of any vote which is void or by any non-compliance with the provisions of any rules of the society.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.-- A person shall be deemed to have committed a corrupt practice who, directly or`
  line `indirectly, by himself or by any other person, --`
  line
  line `(i) induces, or attempts to induce, by fraud, intentional misrepresentation, coercion or threat`
  line `of injury, any elector to give on to refrain from giving a vote in favour of any candidate, or any`
  line `person to stand or not to stand as, or to withdraw or not to withdraw from being a candidate at the`
  line election;
  line
  line `(ii) with a view to inducing any elector to give or to refrain from giving a vote in favour of`
  line `any candidate, or to inducing any person to stand or not to stand as, or to withdraw or not to`
  line `withdraw from being a candidate at the election, offers or gives any money, or valuable`
  line `consideration, or any place or employment, or holds out any promise of individual advantage or`
  line `profit to any person;`
  line
  line `(iii) abets (within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code) the doing of any of the acts`
  line `specified in clauses (i) and (ii);`
  line
  line `(iv) induces or attempts to induce in candidate or elector to believe that he, or any person in`
  line `whom he is interested, will become or will be rendered an object of divine displeasure or spiritual`
  line censure;
  line
  line `(v) canvasses on grounds of caste, community, sect or religion;`
  line
  line `(vi) commits such other practice as the State Government may prescribe to be a corrupt`
  line practice.
  line
  line `Explanation II. -- A promise of individual advantage or profit to a person includes a promise for the`
  line `benefit of the person himself, or of anyone in whom he is interested.`
  line
  line `Explanation III.--- The State Government may prescribe the procedure for hearing and decision of`
  line `doubts or disputes in respect of such elections and make provision in respect of any other matter relating`
  line `to such elections for which insufficient provision exists in this Act or in the rules of the society.`
  line
  line `(2) Where by an order made under sub-section (1) an election is set aside or an office-bearer is held`
  line `no longer entitled to continue in notice or where the Registrar is satisfied that any election of office`
  line `bearers of a society has not been held within the time specified in the rules of that society, he may call a`
  line `meeting of the general body of such society for electing such office bearer or office-bearers, and such`
  line `meeting shal1 be presided over and be conducted by the Registrar or by any officer advisory by him in`
  line `this behalf, and the prescribe the rules of the society relating to meetings and elections shall apply to such`
  line `meeting and election with necessary modifications.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a meeting is called by the Registrar under sub-section (2), no other meeting shall be called`
  line `for the purpose of election by any other authority or by any person claiming to be an office-bearer of the`
  line society.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the expression "prescribed authority" mean, an officer`
  line `or court authorized in this behalf by the State Government by notification published in the Official`
  line Gazette.
  line
  line `25. Terms of gift to be observed.--Where a society accepts a gift or nation of money or property of`
  line `any other kind from any person for a specific purpose, it shall not use the money or other property gifted`
  line `or donated or any part thereof for any other purpose except for the promotion of the activities of the`
  line society.
  line
  line `26. Penalties.--Any society which--`
  line
  line `(a) fails to furnish the list of managing body or other information required to be furnished under`
  line `section 22 or wilfully makes or causes to be made a false entry in, or any omission from, the list or`
  line
  line `any statement or copy of rules or of alteration in rules or other information sent to the Registrar under`
  line `the said section;`
  line
  line `(b) wilfully fails, neglects or refuses to maintain, balance and audit accounts as referred to in`
  line `section 12C;`
  line
  line `(c) wilfully fails to produce any books of accounts or other records as required by sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 23;`
  line
  line `(d) wilfully fails to appear before the Registrar or other person authorised by him or otherwise`
  line `contravenes the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 23;`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `27. Compounding of offences.-- (1) The Registrar may accept from any person against whom a`
  line `reasonable suspicion exists that he has committed any offence punishable under section 26 or against`
  line `whom a prosecution under that section has been instituted, a sum of money by way of composition`
  line `fee for the offence which such person is suspect or accused to have committed.`
  line
  line `(2) On the payment of such composition fee the suspected person shall be discharged and no`
  line `further proceedings shall be taken against him, and if persecution of such composition shall have the`
  line `effect of his acquittal.`
  line
  line `28. Manner of payment of fees.-- Fees payable under the provisions of this Act shall be paid in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `29. Mode of service of notice by Registrar.-- (1) Any notice, order or requisition means for a`
  line `society or for the governing body thereof to be issued by the Registrar may be served on the Secretary`
  line `of the society, and service on the Secretary shall be as effectual as if the same had been served on`
  line `every member of the society or, as the case may be, on every member of the governing body thereof,`
  line `unless the Registrar otherwise directs.`
  line
  line `(2) The sending of such notice, order or requisition to the Secretary of the society by registered`
  line `post at its registered office shall amount to sufficient service thereof on the society.`
  line
  line `30. Appointment of Administrator.-- (1) Where on receipt of a complaint from three office bearers of a society or three affected persons or on inspection of records, the Registrar is satisfied, ---`
  line
  line `(i) that the society is working against the objectives and ideals as per sections 1 and 20 on the`
  line `basis of which the society was granted certificate;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the society is not working democratically or the elections have not taken place within`
  line `the specified time or election taken place fraudulently or against the clauses of memorandum of`
  line association;
  line
  line `(iii) that the office-bears have been nominated against the clause of memorandum of`
  line association;
  line
  line `(iv) that the number of members in a trustee mandal has been purposely kept below seven,`
  line `the Registrar may recommend to the State Government to appoint an Administrator :`
  line
  line `Provided that no adverse order shall be passed unless an opportunity of being heard has been`
  line `given to the concerned society:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the action of the Registrar in this behalf shall be final and no appeal shall lie`
  line `in any court against such action.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, shall appoint an`
  line `Administrator of such society who shall not be below the rank of Deputy Secretary for such period,`
  line `not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the order to manage the affairs of the society :`
  line
  line `Provided that for reasons to be recorded in writing, the State Government may, by like order,`
  line `extend the said period for a further duration of six months (3) On the appointment of the Administration under sub-section (2), the governing body of the`
  line `society shall cease to exercise any powers and perform and discharge any functions or duties`
  line `conferred or imposed on it by this Act, or its memorandum of association or the rules and regulations`
  line `of any other law and subject to any directions which the State Government may from time to time`
  line `issue, all such functions or duties shall be performed or discharged by the Administrator.`
  line
  line `(4) The Administrator shall, before the expiry of the period of his appointment, take necessary`
  line `action to convene the general body meeting of the society and hold election for the constitution of the`
  line `governing body.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Administrator is not, for reasons beyond his controlable to convene the general body`
  line `meeting or inspite of such meeting being convened the general body fails to elect the governing body,`
  line `the Administrator shall forthwith send a report to the State Government who may pass such orders as`
  line `are considered necessary, either extending the period of appointment of the Administrator for a`
  line `further duration or if satisfied that public interest so requires, for the dissolution of the society.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Government may, if it thinks fit, appoint a committee to advise and assist the`
  line `Administrator appointed under sub-section (1) in the exercise of the powers and performance and`
  line `discharge of the duties and functions conferred or imposed on him under this Act. The members of`
  line `the committee shall have such qualifications as may be prescribed and shall hold office during the`
  line `pleasure of the State Government.`
  line
  line `(7) Where an order of dissolution is passed under sub-section (5), the assets of the society shall`
  line `vest in and the liabilities shall devolve on the State Government.`
  line
  line `31. indemnity.-- No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shalt lie in any court against the`
  line `State Government, the Registrar or against any person appointed for inspection or investigation under`
  line `section 23, for anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `32. Power to make rules.--(1) The State Government may, after previous publication, make`
  line `rules not inconsistent with this Act for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the State`
  line `Government may make rules--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribing the form of the register of societies and the mode in which entries relating to`
  line `registration are to be made therein, and the mode in which such entries are to be amended or`
  line `notes made therein;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the filing of documents received by the Registrar;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing the particulars to be contained in the form of accounts under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 12C;`
  line
  line `(d) prescribing the manner in which the accounts shall be audited under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 12C;`
  line
  line `(e) prescribing the authority before whom and the time within which an appeal shall be`
  line `preferred under sub-section (2) of (g) section 12E. and the manner in which such appeal shall be`
  line filed;
  line
  line `(f) prescribing the duties, functions and powers of governing body of the society under`
  line `section 16A;`
  line
  line `(g) prescribing conditions for the inspection of original documents and regulating the grant of`
  line `copies of documents under section 19;`
  line
  line `(h) prescribing the procedure for hearing and decision of doubts or disputes in respect of`
  line `elections under sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(i) prescribing the manner in which fees payable under this Act shall be paid under section`
  line `28 (j) prescribing the qualifications of members of society under sub-section (6), of section 30:`
  line
  line `(k) providing for any other matter for which there is no provision or insufficient provision`
  line `exists in this Act and for which provision is, in the opinion of the State Government, necessary`
  line `for giving effect to the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made, before the`
  line `House of the State Legislature, while it is in session, If the House agrees in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or the House agrees that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 14 of 2007, s. 7]`
  line
  line `22. Procedure.--(1) No Court inferior to that of a Magistrate of the First Class shall try an offence`
  line `punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No Court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this Act except upon complaint`
  line `made by the Registrar of Joint Stock Companies or any other person, authorized in writing by him, in this`
  line `behalf.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam 11 of 1952, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `After section 20, the following sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"21. Penalties.--(1) If the President, Secretary or any other person authorised in this behalf by a`
  line `resolution of the governing body of the society fails to comply with the provisions of section 4A, he`
  line `shall, on conviction be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and in case of a`
  line `continuing breach, shall also be punishable with fine not exceeding fifty rupees for each day, during`
  line `the period the breach continue after the first conviction for such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person willfully makes or causes to be made any false entry in, or any commission from`
  line `the list required by section 4, or in or from any statement or copy of rules or of alterations in rules`
  line `sent to the Registrar under section 4A, he shall, on conviction, be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to two thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `22. Procedure.--(1) No court inferior to that of a Judicial Magistrate of the first class shall try`
  line `any offence punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Judicial Magistrate of the first class for the purposes of this Act means the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner, Additional Deputy Commissioner, Assistant Commissioner and Extra Assistant`
  line `Commissioner who has been empowered under the Assam Frontier (Administration of Just)`
  line `Regulation, 1945 (1 of 1945), to administer justice in the territory of Arunachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(2) No. court shall take congnizance of an offence punishable under this Act except upon`
  line `complaint made by the Registrar or any other person, authorised in writing by him, in this behalf.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam 11 of 1952, s. 3]`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 6 of 1978, s. 2 and the Schedule]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Amendment of section 20 of Act 21 of 1860.--In section 20, for the words and sign, "instruments or`
  line `design", the words and sign "instruments or design, promotion of the interest or welfare of the public and`
  line `any other object as may be notified by the Government as beneficial to the public, shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 23 of 1974, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Insertion of section 22 to 32 in Central Act 21 of 1860.--After section 21 of the principal Act, the`
  line `following sections shall be added at the end, namely:--`
  line
  line `"22. Power of Registrar to call for information.--(1) The Registrar may. by written order,`
  line `require any society to furnish in writing such information or document within such time, being`
  line `ordinarily not less than three weeks from the date of receipt of the order by the society, as he may`
  line `specify in the order in connection with the affairs of the society or any documents filed by the society`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt by the society of an order under sub-section (1), it shall be the duty of the`
  line `President, Secretary or any other person authorized in this behalf to furnish such information or`
  line documents.
  line
  line `23. Investigations of affairs of society.--(1) Where on the information received under section`
  line `22 or otherwise, the Registrar is of opinion that there is apprehension that the affairs of a society`
  line `registered under this Act are being so conducted as to defeat the objects of the society or that the`
  line `society or its governing body by whatever name called, or any office-bearer thereof in actual effective`
  line `control of the society is guilty of mismanaging its affairs or of any breach of fiduciary or other like`
  line `obligations, the Registrar may, either himself or by any person authorized by him in that behalf,`
  line `inspect or investigate into the affairs of the society or inspect any institution managed by the society.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of every office-bearer of the society when so required by the Registrar or`
  line `other person authorised under sub -section (1) to produce any books of account and other records of`
  line `or relating to the society which are in his custody and to give him all assistance in connection with`
  line `such inspection or investigation.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar or other person authorized under sub -section (1) may call upon and examine on`
  line `oath any office -bearer, member or employee of the society in relation to the affairs of the society and`
  line `it shall be the duty of every office -bearer, member or employee, when called upon, to appear before`
  line `him for such examination.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar or other person authorized under sub -section (1) may, if in his opinion it is`
  line `necessary for the purpose of inspection or investigation, seize any or all the records including account`
  line `books of the society:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person from whose custody such records are seized shall be entitled to make`
  line `copies thereof in the presence of the person seizing such records (5) On the conclusion of the`
  line `inspection or investigation, as the case may be, the person, if any, appointed by the Registrar to`
  line `inspect or investigate shall make a report to the Registrar on the result of his inspection or`
  line investigation.
  line
  line `(6) The Registrar may, after such inspection or investigation, give such directions to the society oi`
  line `to its governing body or any office-bearer thereof, as he may think fit. for the removal of any defects`
  line `or irregularities within such time es may be specified and in the event of default in taking action`
  line `according to such directions, the Registrar may proceed to take action under section 12E or`
  line `section 30, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `24. Dispute regarding election of office-bearers.--(1) The prescribed authority may, on a`
  line `refence made to it by the Registrar or by at least one-fourth of the members of a society registered in`
  line `Haryana, meet and decide in a summary manner any doubt or dispute in respect of the election or`
  line `continuance in office of an office-bearer of such society, and may pass such orders in respect thereof`
  line `as it deems fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the election of an office-bearer shall be set aside where the prescribed authority is`
  line satisfied--
  line
  line `(a) that any corrupt has been committed by such office-bearer; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the nomination of any candidate has been improperly rejected; or`
  line
  line `(c) that the result of the election insofar as it concerns to such office -bearer has been`
  line `materially affected by the improper acceptance of any nomination or by the improper reception,`
  line `refusal or rejection of any vote or the reception of any vote which is void or by any noncompliance with the provisions of any rules of the society.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.-- A person shall be deemed to have committed a corrupt practice who, directly or`
  line `indirectly, by himself or by any other person.`
  line
  line `(i) induces, or attempts to induce, by fraud, intentional misrepresentation, coercion or threat`
  line `of injury, any elector to give oi to refrain from giving a vote in favour of any candidate, or any`
  line `person to stand or not to stand as, or to withdraw or not to withdraw from being a candidate at the`
  line election;
  line
  line `(ii) with a view to inducing any elector to give or to refrain from giving a vote in favour of`
  line `any candidate, or to inducing any person to stand or not to stand as, or to withdraw or not to`
  line `withdraw from being a candidate at the election, offers or gives any money. or valuable`
  line `consideration, or any place or employment, or holds out any promise of individual advantage or`
  line `profit to any person;`
  line
  line `(iii) abets (within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code) the doing of any of the acts`
  line `specified in clauses (i) and (ii);`
  line
  line `(iv) induces or attempts to induce it candidate or elector to believe that he, or any person in`
  line `whom he is interested, will become or will De rendered an object of divine displeasure or`
  line `spiritual censure;`
  line
  line `(v) canvasses on grounds of caste, community, sect or religion;`
  line
  line `(vi) commits, Lich other practice as the State Government may prescribe to be a corrupt`
  line practice.
  line
  line `Explanation II.--A promise of individual advantage or profit to a person includes a promise for`
  line `the benefit of the person himself, or of anyone in whom he is interested.`
  line
  line `Explanation III.-- The State Government may prescribe the procedure for hearing and decision of`
  line `doubts or disputes in respect of such elections and make provision in respect of any other matter`
  line `relating to such elections for which insufficient provision exists in this Act or in the rules of the`
  line society.
  line
  line `(2) Where by an order made under sub-section (1), an election is set aside or an office -bearer is`
  line `held no longer entitled to continue in office or where the Registrar is satisfied that any election of`
  line `office bearers of a society has not been held *faun the time specified in the rules of that society, he`
  line `may call a meeting of the general body of such society for electing such office bearer or`
  line `office-bearers, and such meeting shal1 be presided over and be conducted by the Registrar or the`
  line `society relating to meetings and elections shall apply to such meeting and election with necessary`
  line modifications.
  line
  line `(3) Where a meeting is called by the Registrar under sub -section (2), no other meeting shall be`
  line `called for the purpose of election by any other authority or by any person claiming to be an office-bearer of the society.`
  line
  line `Explanation. For the purposes of this section, the expression 'prescribed authority' mean, an`
  line `officer or court authorized in this behalf by the State Government by notification published in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `25. Terms of gift to be observed.--Where a society accepts a gift or donation of money or`
  line `property of any other kind from any person for a specific purpose, it shall not use the money or other`
  line `property gifted or donated or any part thereof for any other purpose except for the promotion of the`
  line `activities of the society.`
  line
  line `26. Penalties.--Any society which--`
  line
  line `(a) fails to furnish the list of managing body or other information required to be furnished`
  line `under section 22 or wilfully makes or causes to be made a false entry in, or any omission from,`
  line `the list or any statement or copy of rules or of alteration in rules or other information sent to the`
  line `Registrar under the said section:`
  line
  line `(b) wilfully fails, neglects or refuses to maintain, balance and audit accounts as referred to in`
  line `section 12C, wilfully fails to produce any books of accounts or other records as required by`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(d) wilfully fails to appear before the Registrar or other person authorised by him or`
  line `otherwise contravenes the provisions of sub -section (3) of section 23;`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `27. Compounding of offences.--(1) The Registrar may accept from any person against whom a`
  line `reasonable suspicion exists that he has committed any offence punishable under section 26 or against`
  line `whom a prosecution under that section has been instituted, a sum of money by way of composition`
  line `fee for the offence which such person is suspect or .1ccused to have committed.`
  line
  line `(2) On the payment of such composition fee the suspected person shall be discharged and no`
  line `further proceedings shall be taken and the composition shall have the effect of his acquittal.`
  line
  line `28. Manner of payment of fees.--Fees payable under the provisions of this Act shall be paid in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `29. Mode of service of notice by Registrar.--(1) Any notice, order or requisition meant for a`
  line `society or for the governing body thereof to be issued by the Registrar may be served on the Secretary`
  line `of the society, and service on the Secretary shall be as effectual as if the same had been served on`
  line `every member of the society or, as the case may be, on every member of the governing body thereof,`
  line `unless the Registrar otherwise directs.`
  line
  line `(2) The sending of such notice, order or requisition to the Secretary of the society by registered`
  line `post at its registered office shall amount to sufficient service thereof on the society.`
  line
  line `30. Appointment of Administrator.-- (I) Where on receipt of a complaint from three`
  line `office-bearers of a society or three affected persons or on inspection of records, the Registrar is`
  line satisfied,--
  line
  line `(i) that the society is working against the objectives and ideals as per sections 1 and 20 on the`
  line `basis of which the society was granted certificate;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the society is not working democratically or the elections have not taken place within`
  line `the specified tune or the election have taken place fraudulently or against the clauses of`
  line `memorandum of association;`
  line
  line `(iii) the office-bearers have been nominated against the clauses of memorandum of`
  line association;
  line
  line `(iv) that the number of members in a trustee mandal has been purposely kept below seven,`
  line `the Registrar may recommend to the State Government to appoint an Administrator :`
  line
  line `Provided that no adverse order shall be passed unless an opportunity of being heard has been`
  line `given to the conceined society:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the action of the Registrar in this behalf shall be final and no appeal shall lie`
  line `in any court against such action.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, shall appoint an`
  line `Administrator of such society who shall not be below the rank of Deputy Secretary for such period,`
  line `not exceeding six months. as may be specified in the order to manage the affairs of the society :`
  line
  line `Provided that for reasons to be recorded in writing, the State Government may, by like order,`
  line `extend the said period for a further duration of six months.`
  line
  line `(3) On the appointment of the Administration under sub -section (2), the governing body of the`
  line `society shall cease to exercise any powers and perform and discharge any functions or duties`
  line `conferred or imposed on it by this Act, or its memorandum of association or the rules and regulations`
  line `of any other law and subject to any directions which the State Government may from time to time`
  line `issue, all such functions or duties shall be performed or discharged by the Administrator.`
  line
  line `(4) The Administrator shall, before the expiry of the period of his appointment, take necessary`
  line `action to convene the general body meeting of the society and hold election for the constitution of the`
  line `governing body.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Administrator is not, for reasons beyond his controllable to convene the general body`
  line `meeting or in spite of such meeting being convened the general body fails to elect the governing`
  line `body, the Administrator shall forthwith send a report to the State Government who may pass such`
  line `orders as are considered necessary, either extending the period of appointment of the Administrator`
  line `for a further duration or if satisfied that public interest so requires, for the dissolution of the society.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Government may, if it thinks fit, appoint a committee to advise and assist the`
  line `Administrator appointed under sub-section (1) in the exercise of the powers and performance and`
  line `discharge of the duties and functions conferred or imposed on him under this Act. The members of`
  line `the committee shall have such qualifications as may he prescribed and shall hold office during the`
  line `pleasure of the State Government.`
  line
  line `(7) Where an order of dissolution is passed under sub-section (5), the assets of the society shall`
  line `vest in and the liabilities shall devolve on the State Government.`
  line
  line `31. indemnity.--No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shalt lie in any court against the`
  line `State Government, the Registrar or against any person appointed for inspection or investigation under`
  line `section 23, for anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `32. Power to make rules.--(1) The State Government may, after previous publication, make rules`
  line `not inconsistent with this Act for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the State Government`
  line `may make rules--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribing the form of the register of societies and the mode in which entries relating to`
  line `registration are to be made therein, and the mode in which such entries are to be amended or notes`
  line `made therein;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the filing of documents received by the Registrar;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing the particulars to be contained in the form of accounts under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section I2C;`
  line
  line `(d) prescribing the manner in which the accounts shall be audited under sub-section (4) of section`
  line 12C;
  line
  line `(e) prescribing the authority before whom and the time within which an appeal shall be preferred`
  line `under sub -section (2) of section 12E and the manner in which such appeal shall be filed;`
  line `(f) prescribing the duties, functions and powers of governing body of the society under section`
  line I6A;
  line
  line `(g) prescribing conditions for the inspection to original documents and regulating the grant of`
  line `copies of documents under section 19;`
  line
  line `(h) prescribing the procedure for hearing and decision of doubts or disputes in respect of elections`
  line `under sub -section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(i) prescribing the manner in which fees payable under this Act shall be paid under section 2S;`
  line
  line `(j) prescribing the qualifications of members of society under sub -section (6), of section 30:`
  line
  line `(k) providing for any other matter for which there is no provision or insufficient provision exists`
  line `in this Act and for which provision is, in the opinion of the State Government necessary for giving`
  line `effect to the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made. before the House`
  line `of the State Legislature, while it is in session, If the House agrees in making any modification in the rule`
  line `or the House agrees that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.ic95623`
